Collection = ::::_____________________________

* If we want to represent a group of individual objects as a single entity then we should go for collection.

Collection interface = :::: _________________________

* Collection interface is the interface which is implemented by all the classes in the collection frameword
* Collection interface define the most common methods are applicable for any collection object 
* Methods : 1) Boolean add(Object obj)   2) Boolean addAll(Collection c)   3) void clear()

Diffrence between collection and collections =:::::::_________________________

* collection is an interface which can be used to represent a group of individual objects as a single entity.
* collections is an class present in java.util package to define several utility method like (searching,sorting) for 
  collection object.
  
